facts.fact_text: US job quits rose to 3.204 million in December 2025.

evidences.evidence_text: The number of job quits in the US rose slightly to 3.204 million in December 2025

facts.fact_text: Job quits in December 2025 were higher than the upwardly revised 3.193 million in November and above 3.095 million a year ago.

evidences.evidence_text: from the upwardly revised 3.193 million in November and above 3.095 million a year ago.

facts.fact_text: The December reading was the highest in six months.

evidences.evidence_text: It was the highest reading in six months.

facts.fact_text: Quits rose primarily in retail trade (+87,000) and information (+28,000).

evidences.evidence_text: Quits rose primarily in retail trade (+87,000) and information (+28,000)

facts.fact_text: Quits fell in professional and business services (-151,000) and private educational services (-19,000).

evidences.evidence_text: but fell in professional and business services (-151,000) and private educational services (-19,000).

facts.fact_text: The quits rate stood at 2% in December, matching November's reading.

evidences.evidence_text: The quits rate, a metric that measures voluntary job leavers as a proportion of total employment, stood at 2% in December, matching November's reading.

facts.fact_text: Job quits increased in the Midwest (+59,000) and the West (+13,000).

evidences.evidence_text: Regionally, job quits increased in the Midwest (+59,000) and the West (+13,000)

facts.fact_text: Job quits declined in the South (-50,000) and the Northeast (-11,000).
